description:
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Clinical Neurophysiology at the Barts Health NHS Trust is inviting applications for an enthusiastic qualified Specialised Clinical Physiologist (band 6) to join a busy team at the Barts Health NHS Trust. The Department is situated at the Royal London Hospital and offers experience in the full range of Clinical Neurophysiology investigations for adults and children from routine EEG recordings, sleep, MSLT and portable EEG and EP recordings (both within the trust and to other regional hospitals). A full Evoked Potential service is provided. Additionally Clinical Physiologist’s undertake peripheral hand clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will be competent practitioners and must have BSc in Clinical Physiology (Neurophysiology) or equivalent, Part I + II and RCCP registration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Barts Health NHS Trust is an equal opportunities employer and is dedicated to improving working lives for all employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameChristopher GreenJob titleNeurophysiology ManagerEmail addresschristopher.green11@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
